Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Learning probability distributions", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779547481190337*^9, 3.779547487269104*^9}, {
  3.813313253659418*^9, 
  3.8133132563292823`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8734c281-6bef-429b-92aa-\
2000ecb17e36"],

Cell["\<\
This chapter presents important techniques in statistics and machine learning \
which allow data to be described in terms of theoretical probability \
distributions or numerically build probability distributions from data. These \
tasks are called \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]find a distribution\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]learn a distribution\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] from data, respectively. Before covering these \
topics in the last two sections of the notebook, an revision of probability \
distributions is given in the first four sections of the notebook. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779701877708239*^9, 3.779701932300939*^9}, {
  3.813955340488245*^9, 3.813955345485056*^9}, {3.882851919678738*^9, 
  3.882852173876461*^9}, {3.8828522173645763`*^9, 
  3.882852248926103*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a96a72ab-3807-4f77-ae7a-\
76c8f29ed695"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Probability distributions revision (optional)", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8828521830363407`*^9, 
  3.882852206397369*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5b577d72-7ee7-4d78-85ce-\
5f6600d8f091"],

Cell["\<\
A revision on probability distributions is given in the next four sections. \
This is included as optional material that you can cover if you feel your \
knowledge about probability distributions is a bit rusty.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.882852254389042*^9, 
  3.88285236396087*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"58d5a5da-94e0-4e47-96e7-\
4584a0849e3e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Random variable", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779683582308551*^9, 
  3.779683585284296*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"732dc8fc-3e93-4780-90df-\
44ef7ec06226"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A random variable (r.v.) is a ",
 StyleBox["numerical",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " description of the outcome of an experiment that involves ",
 StyleBox["randomness",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". \n\nUnlike normal variables such as the weight of a kilogram of potatoes,",
 StyleBox[" random variables do not take a fixed value",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ".\n\nRandom variables are used extensively in sciences. Machine learning is \
not an exception.  "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.8139552823396597`*^9, {3.8139553254660497`*^9, 3.8139553259328065`*^9}, {
   3.813955359539333*^9, 3.8139553739287667`*^9}, {3.81395563745376*^9, 
   3.8139556478825054`*^9}, {3.8139557094343033`*^9, 3.813955765049164*^9}, {
   3.8139558380922747`*^9, 3.813955871055441*^9}, {3.813955943068385*^9, 
   3.8139559439205823`*^9}, {3.813994477162572*^9, 3.8139945207174654`*^9}, {
   3.81399455403853*^9, 
   3.8139945804197884`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"377231d1-6009-4687-a07f-\
d8d7f308b9df"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "There are two types of random variables: ",
 StyleBox["discrete and continuous.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.8139559537391424`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"5d975ea8-0aa2-46aa-85b0-\
1918b059e522"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Discrete r.v.: Can take a countable number of distinct values.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8139558287572637`*^9, 3.813955831935136*^9}, {
  3.8139558795645156`*^9, 3.8139559050069475`*^9}, {3.813955962856566*^9, 
  3.813955971732129*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f73dca5c-d956-4ef4-9c39-\
a98882690d3c"],

Cell["\<\
Examples: Number of children in a randomly selected family, number of e-mails \
received in one day, number of times we win the lottery.\
\>", "SubitemParagraph",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8139558287572637`*^9, 3.813955831935136*^9}, {
  3.8139558795645156`*^9, 3.8139559050069475`*^9}, {3.813955962856566*^9, 
  3.81395597033313*^9}, {3.813956027229767*^9, 3.8139560742775073`*^9}, {
  3.813956179043189*^9, 
  3.8139561802449055`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"35a8440d-1c49-421d-b69c-\
c5d471994034"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Continuous r.v.: Can assume any value in some interval on the real number \
line.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8139558287572637`*^9, 3.813955831935136*^9}, {
  3.8139558795645156`*^9, 3.8139559050069475`*^9}, {3.813955962856566*^9, 
  3.81395597033313*^9}, {3.813956027229767*^9, 
  3.813956150035041*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7eaea00d-8e53-43f0-bdfb-\
7a187e09dd70"],

Cell["\<\
Examples: Weight of a randomly picked orange in the supermarket, rainfall in \
one month, magnitude of an earthquake.\
\>", "SubitemParagraph",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8139558287572637`*^9, 3.813955831935136*^9}, {
   3.8139558795645156`*^9, 3.8139559050069475`*^9}, {3.813955962856566*^9, 
   3.81395597033313*^9}, {3.813956027229767*^9, 3.813956155836729*^9}, 
   3.8139562141207533`*^9, {3.8139562485625525`*^9, 3.813956311511533*^9}, {
   3.8139564913655057`*^9, 
   3.813956503713312*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b2dc7553-badb-4d91-b60a-\
99c56f645c49"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Discrete r.v.", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7796849505680723`*^9, 3.779684955751924*^9}, {
  3.8139581713626595`*^9, 3.8139581777842183`*^9}, {3.8139972019667063`*^9, 
  3.813997207337146*^9}, {3.8139973229835644`*^9, 
  3.813997324753383*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"beca7ad7-7e06-49f0-920e-\
e5e7e60fa03f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Probability distribution", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.813997329409387*^9},ExpressionUUID->"aaae2c44-0401-48fd-97c4-\
9e6871f24209"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let ",
 StyleBox["X",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " be a discrete r.v. taking ",
 StyleBox["K",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " discrete values {",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["x", "1"], ",", 
     SubscriptBox["x", "2"], ",", "...", ",", 
     SubscriptBox["x", "K"]}], "}"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6feda506-3f2e-4c31-9371-c95445dafeb3"],
 "\n\nAny value ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "k"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5e0a5d3d-113e-47b2-baf4-0acc62574245"],
 "occurs with probability ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"P", "(", 
     RowBox[{"X", "=", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "k"]}], ")"}], "=", 
    SubscriptBox["p", "k"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fca87110-2a40-409a-979e-a9b9fb59f041"],
 "\n\nThe probability distribution of ",
 StyleBox["X",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is the list of probabilities for all the possible values of X:\n\n\t\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["p", "1"], ",", 
     SubscriptBox["p", "2"], ",", "...", ",", " ", 
     SubscriptBox["p", "K"]}], "}"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d4133ce8-52ad-4f98-a7fb-642d1e0c0956"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779685070439618*^9, 3.77968516752874*^9}, {
  3.779685237547604*^9, 3.7796852386014137`*^9}, {3.77968568399722*^9, 
  3.779685741934133*^9}, {3.8139565625178413`*^9, 
  3.8139565640370283`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"12d1c1bc-7903-4e42-874b-\
0f82d30265dc"],

Cell["\<\

Some probability distributions appear more frequently in applications than \
other. For the purposes of this course, we will mostly consider the following:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779684817752364*^9, 3.779684887879796*^9}, {
  3.779685755453444*^9, 3.779685804062235*^9}, {3.813956590627759*^9, 
  3.8139566014740725`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"46a8df64-7eb5-47f2-a532-\
e5bfbd038919"],

Cell["Bernoulli distribution", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779684904503367*^9, 3.779684910599927*^9}, {
  3.77968578986944*^9, 
  3.77968579284691*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5d8576b8-7890-4e5a-ae14-\
876201b09c16"],

Cell["Binomial distribution", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779684904503367*^9, 3.779684910599927*^9}, {
  3.77968578986944*^9, 
  3.779685817677732*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6ae126d5-a026-4c81-8ca7-\
3d943463ad7e"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Bernoulli distribution", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813997281168982*^9, 
  3.8139972852417383`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7d2cd4a3-013b-4305-a9cf-\
770b45df0d46"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let us consider a random variable ",
 StyleBox["X",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " the can only take ",
 StyleBox["two values",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ".\n\nIn general, we refer to these two values as ",
 StyleBox["success",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (S) and ",
 StyleBox["failure ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "(F). "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779686107665059*^9, 3.779686143393984*^9}, {
  3.779686197378682*^9, 3.7796862353789988`*^9}, {3.779686344340209*^9, 
  3.77968635030844*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"89f9e115-e34e-4d73-a16a-\
df378239a11e"],

Cell["\<\
Examples: Tossing a coin, winning/losing the lottery, win/lose a prize\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779686362420391*^9, 
  3.779686411538628*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8779cce9-74aa-4da7-ac95-\
98e1c33707ce"],

